00:03:37.529 --> 00:03:39.050
It will become a little more intuitive.

00:03:39.050 --> 00:03:40.605
And we do, we have many videos that go

00:03:40.605 --> 00:03:42.625
into much more depth that explain that.

00:03:42.625 --> 00:03:45.272
Let's do another example of this.

00:03:45.272 --> 00:03:48.999
So here, we have

00:03:48.999 --> 00:03:50.926
y is equal to g of x in purple

00:03:50.926 --> 00:03:52.981
and y is equal to f of x in blue.

00:03:52.981 --> 00:03:54.768
And they say given that f of x

00:03:54.768 --> 00:03:58.820
is equal to square root
of x plus four minus two,

00:03:58.820 --> 00:04:03.820
write an expression for
g of x in terms of x.

00:04:03.823 --> 00:04:05.162
So first, let's me just try to,

00:04:05.162 --> 00:04:07.774
expression for g of x in terms of f of x.

00:04:07.774 --> 00:04:08.633
We can see once again,

00:04:08.633 --> 00:04:10.978
it's just a shifted version of f of x.

00:04:10.978 --> 00:04:13.381
And remember, I'll just
write it in general.

00:04:13.381 --> 00:04:17.578
So g of x is going to be equal to

00:04:17.578 --> 00:04:22.465
f of x minus your horizontal shift

00:04:24.735 --> 00:04:29.613
plus your vertical shift.

00:04:29.613 --> 00:04:31.749
And so to go from f to g,

00:04:31.749 --> 00:04:34.414
what is your horizontal shift?

00:04:34.414 --> 00:04:36.597
Well, your horizontal shift is,

00:04:36.597 --> 00:04:38.176
if you take this point right over here,

00:04:38.176 --> 00:04:42.100
which should map to that point
once we shift everything.

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:45.675
Your horizontal shift is two to the left

00:04:45.675 --> 00:04:48.907
or you could say it's a
negative two horizontal shift.

00:04:48.907 --> 00:04:50.961
So that should be negative two.

00:04:50.961 --> 00:04:53.116
And then, what is a vertical shift?

00:04:53.116 --> 00:04:54.962
Well, a vertical shift is removed,

00:04:54.962 --> 00:04:58.360
we go from y equals negative
two to the y equals three.

00:04:58.360 --> 00:05:01.672
So we're shifting five up.

00:05:01.672 --> 00:05:04.687
So this is a vertical
shift of positive five.

00:05:04.687 --> 00:05:06.823
So your vertical shift is five.

00:05:06.823 --> 00:05:08.095
So if we just want to write g of x

00:05:08.095 --> 00:05:11.628
in terms of f of x like we just
did in the previous example,

00:05:11.628 --> 00:05:16.047
we could say g of x is
going to be equal to f of x

00:05:16.047 --> 00:05:19.751
minus negative two which is x plus two.

00:05:19.751 --> 00:05:22.039
And then we have plus five.

00:05:22.039 --> 00:05:23.583
But that's not what they asked us to do.

00:05:23.583 --> 00:05:25.023
They asked us to write.

00:05:25.023 --> 00:05:26.207
They, whoops.

00:05:26.207 --> 00:05:28.482
They asked us to write an expression

00:05:28.482 --> 00:05:30.607
for g of x in terms of x.

00:05:30.607 --> 00:05:32.104
And so here we're actually gonna use

00:05:32.104 --> 00:05:34.786
the definition of f of x.

00:05:34.786 --> 00:05:36.342
So let me make it clear.

00:05:36.342 --> 00:05:40.147
We know that f of x is going

00:05:40.147 --> 00:05:42.377
to be equal to square root

00:05:42.377 --> 00:05:46.833
of x plus four minus two.

00:05:46.833 --> 00:05:49.635
So given that,

00:05:49.635 --> 00:05:52.513
what is f of x plus two?

00:05:52.513 --> 00:05:56.619
Well, f of x plus two
is going to be equal to,

00:05:56.619 --> 00:05:58.372
everywhere we see an x,
we're gonna replace it

00:05:58.372 --> 00:05:59.672
with an x plus two.

00:05:59.672 --> 00:06:04.672
Square root of x plus two plus four

00:06:05.190 --> 00:06:06.565
minus two

00:06:06.565 --> 00:06:09.350
which is equal to the square root of

00:06:09.350 --> 00:06:13.043
x plus six minus two.

00:06:13.043 --> 00:06:14.228
Well, that's fair enough.

00:06:14.228 --> 00:06:15.691
That's just f of x plus two.

00:06:15.691 --> 00:06:19.310
Now, what is f of x plus two plus five?

00:06:19.310 --> 00:06:24.310
So f of x plus two plus five

00:06:24.652 --> 00:06:28.368
is going to be in this thing
right over here plus five.

00:06:28.368 --> 00:06:31.131
So it's going to be
equal to square root of

00:06:31.131 --> 00:06:33.903
x plus six minus two

00:06:33.903 --> 00:06:37.029
and I'm going to add five,
with a different color.

00:06:37.029 --> 00:06:38.523
So plus five,

00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:40.543
so plus five.

00:06:40.543 --> 00:06:43.249
And so what we end up with

00:06:43.249 --> 00:06:46.255
is going to be square root of

00:06:46.255 --> 00:06:49.157
x plus six minus two plus five

00:06:49.157 --> 00:06:50.840
is going to be plus three.

00:06:50.840 --> 00:06:53.302
So that is equal to g of x.

00:06:53.302 --> 00:06:54.997
Just as a reminder, what do we do here?

00:06:54.997 --> 00:06:58.482
First, I expressed g of
x in terms of f of x.

00:06:58.482 --> 00:07:00.293
Let's say, hey, to get
from f of x to g of x,

00:07:00.293 --> 00:07:01.853
I shift two to the left.

00:07:01.853 --> 00:07:03.068
Two to the left.

00:07:03.068 --> 00:07:05.056
So we're kinda intuitive, plus two

00:07:05.056 --> 00:07:07.305
makes it a shift of two to the left.

00:07:07.305 --> 00:07:10.103
This was minus two would be
shifted two to the right.

00:07:10.103 --> 00:07:12.285
But like I just said in
the previous example,

00:07:12.285 --> 00:07:13.748
it's good to try it some x's

00:07:13.748 --> 00:07:15.559
and to see why that makes sense.

00:07:15.559 --> 00:07:17.219
And then we shifted five up.

00:07:17.219 --> 00:07:19.367
So this was g of x in terms of f of x.

00:07:19.367 --> 00:07:22.547
Then they told us what f of
x actually is in terms of x.

00:07:22.547 --> 00:07:25.543
So we said, "Okay, well,
what is f of x plus two?"

00:07:25.543 --> 00:07:28.248
F of x plus two, we
substituted x plus two for x

00:07:28.248 --> 00:07:29.571
and we got this.

00:07:29.571 --> 00:07:32.961
But g of x is f of x plus two plus five.

00:07:32.961 --> 00:07:35.445
So we took what we figured
out f of x plus two is

00:07:35.445 --> 00:07:38.081
and then we added five
and that's what g of x is.

00:07:38.081 --> 00:07:39.955
And then we are all done.

